    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <actionDate>2015-07-21</actionDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2015-09-03T16:36:42Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>This bill directs the Department of Defense to establish a process by which the commander of a military installation in the United States may authorize a qualifying member of the Armed Forces who is assigned to duty at the installation to carry a concealed personal firearm on the installation if the commander determines it to be necessary as a personal-protection or force-protection measure. </p> <p>The commander of the installation shall consult with appropriate state and local elected officials and take into consideration state and local laws law regarding carrying a concealed personal firearm.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2015-07-21T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
    </summaries>
    <title>A bill to require a process by which members of the Armed Forces may carry a concealed personal firearm on a military installation.</title>
